      "date": "2021-09-23 06:20:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> > Initial testing failed:\n > >\n > > > runtests-ssk@ldiskfs+SharedKey Failure(366s)\n > > - 1(can't cp /etc/hosts to /mnt/lustre/hosts.8181)\n > > https://testing-archive.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/18619/results.html\n > \n > This failure looks like it might be relevant.  OST console error\n > message:\n > \n > tgt_connect_check_sptlrpc()) lustre-OST0000: unauthorized rpc\n > flavor 20222 from 192.168.203.24@tcp, expect 0\n > \n > Let's wait to see how sanity-sec is doing for this patch before\n > landing it.  It seems \"obvious\" for the one line change, but better\n > to make sure it is working properly.\n\nThis issue shows up on occasions, it is not really new and certainly not specific to this patch, see LU-13116 for instance. I thought I had fixed the problem, but it seems there are still special circumstances under which it occurs :/",
